Content:
General observation about <i>until</i>.  I think it works better "linguistically" as a REPEAT/UNTIL (ala BASIC) and not as a negative <i>while</i> loop.<p>So block of code always gets run at least once.  For eg. in Perl:<p><pre><code>    my $x;
    do { 
        print "guess the number? ";
        $x = readline;
    } until $x == 10;
</code></pre>
Disclaimer:  Can't recall using <i>until</i> since I last played with BASIC.  And that was many years ago :)
